<!-- break -->
<h2>Foreword</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<p>
	So, here's a list of some IoT devices suggested by the students today in
	class, and some characteristics that make them so cool and different
	from normal, non-broke, devices without internet access. Enjoy.
	</p>
</div>

<h1>Main list</h1>
<h2>Smart fridge</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Remote control and configuration</li>
		<li>Inventory management</li>
		<li>Recipe suggestions</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart lights</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Voice-activation</li>
		<li>Remote control via voice or smartphone apps</li>
		<li>Color and/or brightness adjustment</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smartwatch</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Touchscreen</li>
		<li>Can run mobile apps</li>
		<li>Essentially, a portable computer or smartphone</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart microwave</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Control via voice commands</li>
		<li>Can be connected to a mobile app</li>
		<li>Features like auto-defrost, and some presets</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart washing machine</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Allows for greater customization</li>
		<li>Can be controlled remotely</li>
		<li>Features energy efficiency control</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart security alarm</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Can be integrated into a smart security system</li>
		<li>Can be accessed... (guess)... remotely</li>
		<li>
		Motion detection and other sensors whose activation may be
		monitored through an app or whatever
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Alexa</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Has no "dumb" counterpart</li>
		<li>Can set up alarms and perform some other tasks</li>
		<li>Voice-controled</li>
		<li>Can be used to control other devices</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Siri Assitant</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Implemented into Apple platforms</li>
		<li>Controled via voice and text prompts</li>
		<li>
		Performs searches and answers questions, among other functions
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart earbuds (e.g. <i>Galaxy Buds</i>)</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Remotely controlled</li>
		<li>Features GPS location via an account ID</li>
		<li>Can be monitored and charged by a linked smartphone</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart printer</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Connected to the internet</li>
		<li>Can be prompted to print documents wirelessly</li>
		<li>
		May include features like scanning and faxing (via the
		interwebbbs)
		</li>
		<li>
		Gets updates that help the manufacturer take advantage of the
		owner
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Tablet</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Larger than a phone</li>
		<li>Can be used to read books and CONSUME other media</li>
		<li>Able to run applications</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart TV</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Connects to the internet, as usual.</li>
		<li>
		Can be used for more than watching TV, like browsing the
		interwebbbbb, streaming videos and so on.
		</li>
		<li>Essentially a smart phone <em>embedded</em> into a TV</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart mirror</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>In contrast to normal mirrors, this is an abomination</li>
		<li>
		Apart from a reflection, shows information such as the
		weather, time and notifications
		</li>
		<li>
		May be able to be integrated into a smart home environment
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>

<h1>But wait, there's more!</h1>
<div class=bluebox>
	<p>
	Here's a list of five more IoT devices which have no right to exist.
	<strong>ENJOY</strong>.
	</p>
</div>
<h2>Smart water bottle (HidrateSpark)</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Glows to remind the owner that it's time for drinkies</li>
		<li>It could have, like, GPS or something</li>
		<li>I guess it has to be connected to an app or something</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart egg tray (Egg Minder)</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Keeps track of eggs</li>
		<li>Monitors eggs</li>
		<li>Makes you think about eggs</li>
		<li>Eggs</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart condom (i.Con)</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>It's connected to the network</li>
		<li>It's wrapped around your micropenis</li>
		<li>Vibrates or something, I don't know honestly</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart (not really) juice box puncturer and extractor (Juicero)</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Never made it to completion (thankfully)</li>
		<li>Punctures a juice box or bag</li>
		<li>Huh</li>
	</ul>
</div>
<h2>Smart flip-flops</h2>
<div class=bluebox>
	<ul>
		<li>Connected TO THE INTERNET</li>
		<li>It's just a wearable advertisement... thing</li>
		<li>
		Really, it just tracks your gait or something and then
		informs you about discounts or something
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>
